body:
Hi @kl0u, IMO that is the expected behavior. The sink would not know that if the Redis is down or not unless it tries to send the next data to the Redis. When ever a new message reaches the sink it tries to use the connection pool, then an then only it can throw exception that it can not send the data to Redis.
You can build a heartbeat mechanism to check periodically that Redis serve is up or down, and can cancel the job if Redis is down. 
@mjsax please correct me if my understanding is wrong.
